    "reason": "The current prompt is cluttered with negative constraints and warnings. A cleaner, more direct prompt that explicitly limits the helper count and provides a clear, single-example structure will likely reduce both JSON formatting errors and the 'max_helpers' violation. We will move the constraint about the number of helpers to a more prominent position.",
    "new_prompt_text": "Break the problem into a small number of genuinely useful subproblems for other agents. \n\nTo ensure correctness, instruct helpers to perform rigorous mathematical verification (e.g., checking modular constraints, testing small cases, or proving impossibility) rather than just providing intuitive guesses. Each helper should receive one focused mathematical task that builds toward the final solution.\n\nConstraints:\n1. Use a maximum of 2 helpers.\n2. Do not restate the original question in multiple ways.\n3. Use plain text only inside helper instructions. Do not use markdown, code fences, or LaTeX-style backslashes.\n4. Return only valid raw JSON. Do not use markdown code fences (e.g., no ```json). The response must start with { and end with }.\n\nReturn exactly one JSON object in this format:\n{\n  \"schema_name\": \"eywa_node_response\",\n  \"schema_version\": \"v1\",\n  \"orchestration_decision\": \"delegate\",\n  \"decision_notes\": \"optional string\",\n  \"helpers\": [\n    {\n      \"label\": \"helper_1\",\n      \"instructions\": \"plain-text subproblem for the first helper\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"synthesis_brief\": \"how the parent should combine the child results\"\n}"
  },
